---
title: Pork Sausage Rigatoni Rosa with Philadelphia Cream Cheese, Zucchini & Parm
description: Fun culinary and language fact: “Rosa” means “pink” in Italian. For our chefs’ version of rigatoni rosa, you’ll make a homemade rosa sauce with tomato paste, cream cheese, broth, and chili flakes (for a little heat!). Toss that with rigatoni, zucchini, and crumbled pork sausage, then sprinkle Parmesan all over and we promise: you’ll be blushing from all the compliments you receive on this meal.
